http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Thiruvananthapuram/SBT-terms-staff-stir-unjustified/article13985714.ece

The State Bank of Travancore (SBT) management has termed unjustified the one-day strike called by the State Sector Banks Employees Association (SSBEA), an affiliate of the All India Bank Employees Association (AIBEA), in SBT and other associate banks of State Bank of India (SBI), on January 8.A press note by the management on Wednesday said the strike against implementation of the recently introduced Career Progression Scheme for clerical staff in the bank and against imposition of SBI’s service conditions on them had no justification as the Career Progression Scheme is purely optional and under successful implementation in SBI in 2009. The scheme has been received well and is accompanied by substantial monetary benefits to the employees. “While SSBEA of Associate Banks desired that all benefits which are made available to SBI employee be made available to them, they are not willing to accept similar service conditions despite huge benefits to customers and employees,” the management said. It also appealed to appealed to employees of State Bank of Travancore not to participate in the strike.